description:
SecM: Table storing Security Management (SecM) data for specific Ericsson cells, including timestamps, area name, cell IDs, and data format version information.
dateTime: Timestamp of the SecM data record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell site.
Id2: Redundant cell identifier (appears to duplicate CellId).
Id3: An identifier (purpose unclear from sample data).
vsDataType: Type of data (SecM).
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the Ericsson-specific SecM data format.
SecM.secMId:  A unique identifier for the SecM data entry.
queries: Show me all SecM entries from Area_Name 'Downtown' with vsDataFormatVersion 2.0.
What is the maximum dateTime value for SecM records where CellId is 12345?
Retrieve all distinct Area_Name values from the SecM table.
Find all SecM entries with a dateTime between 2024-03-08 00:00:00 and 2024-03-08 23:59:59.
How many SecM records have a matching CellId and Id2, but a different Id3 value?
